1.title: What's inside a Baseball?
1.plot: We cut a Major League baseball in half to see whats inside. This is part of 2nd grader Lincoln's school project. This is an official major league Rawlings baseball.

2.title: What's inside a Golf Ball?
2.plot: Ever wonder what's inside of a Golf Ball? We cut open a Titliest PROV1 golf ball. School project and we had a good time. I love to golf and this is the ball i use. Interesting that golf balls have unique insides.

3.title: What's inside a Tennis Ball?
3.plot: Ever wonder what is inside of a Tennis Ball? We did. We cut open a new Wilson tennis ball to find out for a 2nd grade school project.

4.title: What's inside a Soccer Ball?
4.plot: Ever wonder what is inside of a Soccer Ball, or Football for those outside of the US? We did. We cut open a soccer ball for a 2nd grade project.This is a brand new Wilson soccer ball.

5.title: What's inside a Basketball?
5.plot: Ever wonder what is inside a Basketball? We did. We cut open a basketball for a 2nd grade project. This is a Spalding indoor/outdoor ball.

6.title: Reverse It!
6.plot: With 4 hours to burn Saturday we took some video of us doing things and then played them backwards.

7.title: What's inside a Cricket Ball?
7.plot: What's Inside a Cricket Ball? We were asked by a subscriber to cut open a cock ball (cricket ball) so we did and it was an interesting one. I especially like the "Sad Face" my daughter noticed on the inside of the ball.

8.title: What's inside a Lacrosse Ball?
8.plot: Ever wondered what is inside of an Official Lacrosse ball? We did and wanted to see. Cutting it open is similar to the quote of "making sausage" It is not the prettiest process. But we cut it open so you don't have to.

9.title: What's inside a Volleyball?
9.plot: We were wondering what is inside of a Volleyball so we cut one open. Interesting to see what was inside.

10.title: What's inside a Football?
10.plot: Ever wonder what is inside an American Football? We did so we bought an NFL size football and decided to cut it open. Hope you enjoy finding out what is inside.

11.title: What's inside a Handball?
11.plot: What's inside a Handball? We were asked to cut open this tough ball from an Olympic sport of handball. Very interesting and fun to find out what is inside.

12.title: What's inside a Hockey Puck?
12.plot: Ever wonder what is inside a Hockey Puck? We did so we found a saw and sliced the puck in half.

13.title: What's inside a Tetherball?
13.plot: Ever wonder what is inside a Tetherball? We decided to buy one and cut it open to see for ourselves.

14.title: What's inside a Rugby Ball?
14.plot: We were asked to cut open a Rugby Ball to see what the inside looks like.

15.title: What's inside a Billiard Ball?
15.plot: We wanted to know what is inside a Pool ball so we cut it open. This was a very requested ball to cut open.

16.title: What's inside a Bowling Ball?
16.plot: Ever wonder what is inside of a bowling ball? We bought an electric saw and cut it open for your to enjoy. I am not a pro bowler or a pro at cutting things open but we managed to get the job done.

17.title: What's inside a Field Hockey Ball?
17.plot: Ever wonder what is inside a field hockey ball? We did so we cut open a field hockey ball and it was very interesting. It took us three tries to get it open but now we know what's inside the ball.

18.title: What's inside a Golf Driver Head?
18.plot: We cut open the head of two golf drivers to see how they are made. It was a fun and dangerous task.

19.title: What's inside a Waboba Ball?
19.plot: Ever wonder what's inside a Waboba Ball? We cut one open to find out. We didn't even know what a Waboba ball was until one of our subscribers asked us to cut it open.

20.title: What's inside a Magic 8 Ball?
20.plot: What's inside a Magic 8 Ball? We wanted to see where the magic comes from so we cut this one in half.

21.title: What's inside a Water Polo Ball?
21.plot: Ever wonder what's inside a Water Polo Ball? We cut open a water polo ball for you to enjoy.

22.title: What's inside a Shot Put Ball?
22.plot: We cut a shot put ball in half to see what is inside. This is an 8 pound Portapit shot but ball and it was quite a challenge.

23.title: What's inside a Fushigi Ball?
23.plot: Ever wonder what's inside a Fushigi ball? We cut one open to see the inside. This ball is used for the mysterious art of contact juggling.

24.title: What's inside a Punching Bag?
24.plot: Ever wonder what's inside a Punching Bag? We did so we cut one open. It was full of interesting things. Boxing is a tough sport and these Everest boxing bags take a beating from the athletes.

25.title: What's inside a Wood Baseball Bat?
25.plot: What's inside a Wood Baseball Bat? We cut open a Louisville Slugger official Major League Baseball bat to see what it is made of.

26.title: What's inside a TV?
26.plot: What's inside a TV? We took a Sony projection television and cut it in half to see what it is made of. It was interesting and a lot of fun. In the future we may cut open a flat screen LCD or Plasma tv but a projection tv was quite interesting.

27.title: What's inside a Bowling Pin?
27.plot: Ever wonder what is inside a Bowling Pin? We did so we cut one in half. This is a brand new Brunswick bowling pin used for cosmic bowling.

28.title: What's inside a Giant Jawbreaker?
28.plot: What does the inside of a giant jawbreaker look like when cut in half? We decided to find out. We could have smashed it on the ground and seen the pieces but I wanted a clean cut down the middle.

29.title: What's inside an Electric Guitar?
29.plot: Curious to see what the inside of an electric guitar looks like so we took a saw to it. Is it plastic? Wood? Hollow? We figured it out and had some fun. Come learn as we did. This Guitar is a Hammer Slammer not a Fender guitar but it played really nice.

30.title: What's inside a Globe?
30.plot: What's inside a Globe? A globe of the earth is fun to explore and spin around but what does the inside of it look like? Many of our subscribers have recommended we cut open a globe.

31.title: What's inside a Football Helmet?
31.plot: We were wondering what is inside a football helmet so we cut one in half. This is a game worn NCAA Riddell helmet. We are big fans of BYU so we chose to go there to get a helmet to cut open. NFL and NCAA football will be starting soon. It is amazing that such a small amount of plastic is keeping NFL and College players from Concussions.

32.title: What's inside a Metal Baseball Bat?
32.plot: What's inside a Metal Baseball Bat? We cut one open to see this inside. One is a Rawlings Plasma 32 inch 28 ounce bat while they other is a kids bat, Easton 27 inches long. Before we cut them open we had some fun with them and hit some peaches rather than baseballs.

33.title: What's inside a Lucky Cat?
33.plot: Ever wonder what keeps a Lucky Cat or Maneki-Neko waving it's arm for days? I went to Japan and bought one to cut open and find out. These cats are a lucky charm to bring you good fortune or wealth in Japan and China. You typically see them in the entrance of stores.

34.title: What's inside an Exploding Golf Ball?
34.plot: Ever see a gag video of an exploding golf ball and wonder what in the world are those made of? We did so we bought one and cut it open.

35.title: What's inside a Snow Globe?
35.plot: We went to Santa Clause house in North pole to cut open a Snow Globe. Time to see what makes this work.

36.title: What's inside a Kaleidoscope?
36.plot: We traveled to Seattle and found a Kaleidoscope and want to see what it is made of. We cut it open so you we could learn and also so you can see the interesting things that make up a Kaleidoscope.

37.title: What's inside a Mattress?
37.plot: We cut our mattress in our master bedroom in half to see what it looks like. It was very interesting. We cut things in half so you don't have to.

38.title: What's inside a Rubik's Cube?
38.plot: We cut open, smashed open and pulled open 4 different Rubik's Cubes to see what they are made of. This was really fun and interesting.

39.title: What's inside a Coconut?
39.plot: It isn't easy to cut open a Coconut but we took a saw to one and pried one open. I was in Guam and the locals told me about these coconuts in the market that you can mail to yourself. It was strange but I mailed a coconut in the US mail not in a box or anything.

40.title: What's inside a Baseball Base?
40.plot: We went to Comerica Park in Detroit Michigan to get a game used Baseball base to cut open to see what's inside. This bag was used when the Tigers played the New York Yankees.

41.title: What's inside BB-8?
41.plot: The new Star Wars Movie "The Force Awakens" is premiering December 18 2015 and features a new robot named "BB-8". It is not computer animated and Sphero sells a toy replica that is a BLAST to play with.

42.title: What's inside a Self Balancing Scooter?
42.plot: Ever wonder how these, Hover board, Nano scooters work? We did so we cut one and took it apart. They are so much fun to ride whether around the house or outside.

43.title: What's inside RC Cars?
43.plot: RC cars are so fun to play with. We wanted to take one apart to see what they look like on the inside. We were able to find what we think are the coolest remote control cars. We played with at 21st century type RC Car, R.E.V. or Robotic Enhanced Vehicles. We could have played with them for days but we cut one open so you can see what it looks like inside.

44.title: What's inside a Grenade?
44.plot: What does the inside of a Grenade look like? We cut two open to see. We cut open an apple grenade and a pineapple grenade. They were not live grenades but still gave us a good idea of what it looks like inside and how they work.

45.title: What's inside a Giant Wasp Nest?
45.plot: Ever wondered what's inside a Wasp Nest? We cut this GIANT one in half. We bought it on Ebay and it is huge. Kind of gross honestly but Awesome at the same time.

46.title: What's inside the YouTube Silver Play Button?
46.plot: Let's cut this award in half. We earned the Silver Play Button for reaching 100,000 YouTube Subscribers. We have to continue doing the thing that makes this channel go. We are the first YouTube channel to saw open a play button. Don't worry, we had a little fun with it first and took it to Disneyland.

47.title: What's inside an Xbox One Elite Controller?
47.plot: Let's cut open the hard to come by and CUSTOM Xbox One Elite Controller. We've wondered what they look like inside so we cut this one open. This controller was custom designed by Controller Chaos. Take your gaming to another level by buying your own Controller Chaos featuring your favorite YouTube Gamer or Game.

48.title: What's inside Maracas?
48.plot: You have played with Maracas before, we decided to cut one open and see what's inside. We traveled to Ensenada Mexico to get these authentic Maracas. We had a blast on our first trip to Mexico and we were surprised to see what makes the loud noise when you shake the maracas.

49.title: What's inside a Levitating Speaker?
49.plot: I saw this Air 2 Levitating Bluetooth Speakers and just had to take it apart to see what's inside. We broke it down and LOVED what we found. Air 2 speaker won the 2015 Innovation award at CES (Consumer Electronics Trade show). The speaker plays music up to 12 hours on a full charge and floats while it plays. I enjoy just looking at it without the music playing.

50.title: What's inside a Boosted Board?
50.plot: How does an Electric Skateboard work?? We cut a Boosted Board in half. This was not fun to cut in half because it is such a fun toy.

51.title: What's inside a Rainstick?
51.plot: We cut open a Rainstick to see what it looks like inside. So interesting to learn how it is made. We bought this authentic rainstick in New Mexico while there for the Albuquerque Balloon Fiesta. Rainsticks have been used for many years, since the Aztec people used them to summon a rain storm.

52.title: What's inside a Fire Extinguisher?
52.plot: We cut open a Fire extinguisher to see how it works. First we had to test it and have some fun.

53.title: What's inside a Geode?
53.plot: We cut open a Geode to learn what it looks like inside. Geodes are very unique and cutting one open requires a special stone saw. Thanks to our friend Frank in Alaska we were able to cut some open and learn a few things about rocks and minerals.

54.title: What's inside a Bulletproof Vest?
54.plot: We cut open a Bulletproof Vest to learn what it looks like inside. Before we cut it open we had some fun with the vest to test how effective they are. There are different types bulletproof vests, Ballistic vests or Bullet-resistant vests, the white vest we used is made by "Safari Land" and the Police vest is made by "Point Blank". We bought the Police vest off eBay.

55.title: What's inside a Refrigerator?
55.plot: We cut open a Refrigerator to learn what it looks like inside. Before we cut it open we had some fun with the fridge to test how effective it is, Fridge sledding anyone??? Big thanks to our friend Shonduras for providing his old fridge, and filming the "Behind the Scenes" for this video. It was epic.

56.title: What's inside a Lokai Bracelet?
56.plot: Is there really water and mud in the Lokai Bracelet?? We cut open 5 Lokai Bracelets to find out for ourselves. We were shocked at the results.

57.title: What's inside a Nerf Gun?
57.plot: These Rival Zeus Nerf Guns have some power. We cut one open to see how it works. We had some fun with them first.
